The paper discusses the design and implementation of a neuromorphic processor for spiking neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE). The focus on binary-weight quantization and power efficiency suggests a potential fit for the embedded systems (cs.ET) and architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories. The use of online learning and spike-driven synaptic plasticity also suggests a potential fit for the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
